        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         For skill ups, it is inadviseable to use actual words. Takes too long to find the right words to be practical. If you want skill ups there are two methods:</P><P>1) use the guild trainer and your points. Most people have a whack of unspent points anyhow, and since you cannot train in trade skills over a skill of 20, what else are you going to do with them?</P><P>2) Do the concordence of research quests. You gather a bunch of fairly common items to make runes to do the combines for your skill up reseach practice. A bit of a pain, but doable, and a much better alternative to using real words. Sorry, I no longer have any additional information on these quests to help you with, but a bit of web-research should land you the info pretty quick.</P><P>3) There are so many necros out there with high reseach skills which do nothing but rot. It might seem lazy, but there are more then enough necros out there to do the combines for you any time you need, so forgetting about raising your research skill is another solid choice. If you need a critical spell researched, send me a tell. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P></P><P><BR>Edited by - Ancagalon on 07/21/2002  03:13:16<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
